Ignoring the stacking issues, the benefits of FS over BoF are:<br>
<br>
1) Low cast time - so low that you can tank lowbie mobs by chain casting it and never take a hit.<br>
<br>
2) For those that don't have epic.  Even for a wizard who *wants* their epic, the game has changed these days, and most guilds see any epic but cleric as a waste of time.  So if you're an upcoming new wizard, you may never see your epic, and Force Shield is supposed to make up for that.<br>
<br>
The benefits of BoF over FS:<br>
<br>
1) Very slightly (almost unnoticeable) better - 50hp and 1 mana/tick.<br>
<br>
2) Mana-free.  If you're in a situation where you're getting hurt a lot from continuous pulls of some sort or another that might be AEing you or something, clicking epic between pulls is a lot cheaper than casting FS between pulls, even if you're swapping it in from a bag in place of an FT10 item.<br>
<br>
But overall, they're basically the exact same spell, just one is faster casting with a slight downgrade to it's stats.  If one stacks with SP, the other should too.  If (as implied by the lucy quote above?) they now stack with each other, that would be incredible, but unlikely to be anything but a mistake. <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3741</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 12031<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/14/03 10:40:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25369.topic&index=60>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forge</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If a beastlord is around, use force shield. If not, use epic. its really that simple. Also if your epic is bagged and you have endless cash for dots, then just use force shield all the time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Dots aren't used: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3301&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=25369.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezb